#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "`ini_file` module"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:31
msgid ""
"When you want to modify an INI file (section between `[]` then `key=value` "
"pairs), the easiest way is to use the `ini_file` module."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:33
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:58
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:77
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:96
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:113
msgid "!!! Note"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "    More information can be [found here](https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/collections/community/general/ini_file_module.html).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:37
msgid "The module requires:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:41
msgid "The value of the section"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:41
msgid "The name of the option"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:41
msgid "The new value"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:43
msgid "Example of use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:44
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"- name: change value on inifile\n"
"  community.general.ini_file:\n"
"    dest: /path/to/file.ini\n"
"    section: SECTIONNAME\n"
"    option: OPTIONNAME\n"
"    value: NEWVALUE\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:53
#, no-wrap
msgid "`lineinfile` module"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:56
msgid ""
"To ensure that a line is present in a file, or when a single line in a file "
"needs to be added or modified, use the `linefile` module."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:60
#, no-wrap
msgid "    More information can be [found here](https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/collections/ansible/builtin/lineinfile_module.html).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:62
msgid ""
"In this case, the line to be modified in a file will be found using a regexp."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:64
msgid ""
"For example, to ensure that the line starting with `SELINUX=` in the `/etc/"
"selinux/config` file contains the value `enforcing`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:65
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"- ansible.builtin.lineinfile:\n"
"    path: /etc/selinux/config\n"
"    regexp: '^SELINUX='\n"
"    line: 'SELINUX=enforcing'\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:72
#, no-wrap
msgid "`copy` module"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:75
msgid ""
"When a file has to be copied from the Ansible server to one or more hosts, "
"it is better to use the `copy` module."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "    More information can be [found here](https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/collections/ansible/builtin/copy_module.html).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:81
msgid "Here we are copying `myflile.conf` from one location to another:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:82
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"- ansible.builtin.copy:\n"
"    src: /data/ansible/sources/myfile.conf\n"
"    dest: /etc/myfile.conf\n"
"    owner: root\n"
"    group: root\n"
"    mode: 0644\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:91
#, no-wrap
msgid "`fetch` module"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:94
msgid ""
"When a file has to be copied from a remote server to the local server, it is "
"best to use the `fetch` module."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "    More information can be [found here](https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/collections/ansible/builtin/fetch_module.html).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:100
msgid "This module does the opposite of the `copy` module:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:101
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"- ansible.builtin.fetch:\n"
"    src: /etc/myfile.conf\n"
"    dest: /data/ansible/backup/myfile-{{ inventory_hostname }}.conf\n"
"    flat: yes\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:108
#, no-wrap
msgid "`template` module"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:111
msgid ""
"Ansible and its `template` module use the **Jinja2** template system (http://"
"jinja.pocoo.org/docs/) to generate files on target hosts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:115
#, no-wrap
msgid "    More information can be [found here](https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/collections/ansible/builtin/template_module.html).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:117
msgid "For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:118
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"- ansible.builtin.template:\n"
"    src: /data/ansible/templates/monfichier.j2\n"
"    dest: /etc/myfile.conf\n"
"    owner: root\n"
"    group: root\n"
"    mode: 0644\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:128
msgid ""
"It is possible to add a validation step if the targeted service allows it "
"(for example apache with the command `apachectl -t`):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:129
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"- template:\n"
"    src: /data/ansible/templates/vhost.j2\n"
"    dest: /etc/httpd/sites-available/vhost.conf\n"
"    owner: root\n"
"    group: root\n"
"    mode: 0644\n"
"    validate: '/usr/sbin/apachectl -t'\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:139
#, no-wrap
msgid "`get_url` module"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:142
msgid ""
"To upload files from a web site or ftp to one or more hosts, use the "
"`get_url` module:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:143
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"- get_url:\n"
"    url: http://site.com/archive.zip\n"
"    dest: /tmp/archive.zip\n"
"    mode: 0640\n"
"    checksum: sha256:f772bd36185515581aa9a2e4b38fb97940ff28764900ba708e68286121770e9a\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:151
msgid ""
"By providing a checksum of the file, the file will not be re-downloaded if "
"it is already present at the destination location and its checksum matches "
"the value provided."
msgstr ""
